<#
.SYNOPSIS
   This powerShell script configures system to Audit Account Logon Credential Validation Failures. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.
   By default Windows Systems have no audit logs for Validation Logon failures. 

.NOTES
    Author          : Andres Torres
    LinkedIn        : linkedin.com/in/andres-torres-richardson
    GitHub          : github.com/CyberTechTorres
    Date Created    : 2025-11-15
    Last Modified   : 2025-11-15
    Version         : 1.0
    CVEs            : N/A
    Plugin IDs      : N/A
    STIG-ID         : WN11-AU-000005

.TESTED ON
    Date(s) Tested  : 2025-11-15  
    Tested By       : Andres Torres
    Systems Tested  : "STIG-Andres"
    PowerShell Ver. : 5.1.26100.7019

.USAGE
    Put any usage instructions here.
    Example syntax:
    PS C:\> .\STIG:WN11-AU-000005.ps1
#>
# Enable auditing of Account Logon - Credential Validation failures
auditpol.exe /set /subcategory:"Credential Validation" /failure:enable

# Optional: Verify the policy is set correctly
auditpol.exe /get /subcategory:"Credential Validation"

# Optional: Verify the policy is set correctly
# Open a Command Prompt with elevated privileges
# Run: AuditPol /get /category:*
# Look for Subcategory "Account Logon - Credential Validation"
# Verify "Credential Validation : Failure"
